description:
The property is located in the rural region of Divino de Sao Lourenco, a tourist region that is situated next to the natural park of Caparao with many beautiful waterfalls, hundreds of hiking and cycling trails and the best coffee of Brazil that’s plant here in small scales. 
Part of the property is inside of the natural park and encompasses a nursery of native tree seedlings of the rain forest (Atlantic forest) ecosystem. 

I am streetartist (Instagram: Marombarts), passionate world traveler and cook, storyteller and organic gardener (permaculture). I have lived on this property with at about 36 hectares for 20 years and I managed to reforest a large part of it by planting coffee inside the forest with the help of my wife and people who come to visit me.
Cultural exchange and learning opportunities
+ Learn about coffee plantation in the forest and Agrofloresting;
+ Enjoy meet locals;                                                                                                                         
+ Learn portuguese language;
+ Learn about the local culture;
+ Learn about streetarts, 
+ Enjoy nature trails and waterfalls;
+ Enjoy eating and cooking tradition meal;
+ And much more like some skill of gardening in the forest, Brazilian cooking recipes, unconventional food plants, Bioconstruction, etc...
We need help with: several maintenance and cultivation activities, including: collecting native seeds in the native forests; sowing; seedling pickling and potting; monitoring the growth of the seedlings; planting activities in forest fragmentsproduction of native species conservation and food for subsistence planting and maintenance organic coffee, plant trees, bioconstruction project, etc...
