BBC Organic Farm is an organic farm run by the Borneo Biodiversity Center(BBC). We plant vegetables, herbs and fruit trees from the rainforest(some endangered) as a means to conserve biodiversity. We conduct guided tours on the farm when we reach a certain collection level of the jungle trees. We run a cafe to cook junge recipes that are displaced by commercial joints. We plan the farm as a socio-economic project to uplift rural economy-by converting their knowledge of jungle trees into incomes through guiding tours and selling the seeds/seedlings of valuable jungle plants. We build bamboo house & tree houses as a means of accommodating volunteers and visitors/tourists as well as paying tribute to villagers' expertise in bamboo craft.

Certifications: Organic status is guaranteed by round the clock access and monitoring by volunteers and community members.

Current projects: 1.planting vegetables, including constructing a roof-top garden;

2.collecting jungle fruit trees from all over Borneo;

3.planting herbs in a herb garden;

4.constructing tree houses

5.landscaping;

Internet access available

This is a family-owned chemical-free sustainable veganic organic orchard in California, specializing in growing organic citrus, avocados, herbs, and succulents on 20 acres in Somis, Ventura County, Southern California, USA.

We are a family of two adults, two young adults, and a child.

We would like to teach WWOOFers about thinking outside of the box and not just following the recommendations of agro-industry in order to: 
- Break the chemical cycle of modern agriculture;
- Grow chemical-free food that is so nutritious it is medicine;
- Utilize veganic animal-free farming methods; 
- Increase the health of soil, biodiversity, and well-being of all species.

We are looking for people with strong backs, who can work outside, carry heavy objects and use various tools :) 

We will provide ingredients to make meals. We eat some meals together and some separately depending on people's schedules. Accommodations might vary depending on individual people's needs.

We like cooking, hiking, making music, making films, reading, gardening :)

///// Who are we /////

I'm a dad with a 1,5 year old son, and a cute flock of chickens, spending most of our time in a cabin in the forest. We do our best to foster a regenerative lifestyle in harmony with nature, reusing commodities and pragmatically reducing waste as much as we can. Have had this property for about 2 years now, and so naturally quite a lot of cool things are established but there's plenty of new projects to develop. With a small child, it has also taken us a bit longer to develop in the multitude of aspects of life simultaneously. Tried starting a company too (mostly external landscaping projects), but haven't managed to scale it up or live from it as of now. We produce a variety of fresh food, and we are doing our best to increase the production volume gradually 🌲

///// summary of the situation here & what is needed the most  ///

You'll get a free place to sleep in a peaceful location, eat as much as you want of what we have in stock, and you can borrow bikes and cars for free so you can explore where you want - but you have to refuel your own fuel consumption etc. We have two guest rooms. So we can host two people with know prior acquaintance, or if two groups of two wish to visit at the same time the maximum capacity (to ensure it is comfortable for everyone) is 4 guests. Not enough space for more people than that unless you're experienced and happy with tenting or have a campervan 🏠

The tasks available can range from pretty complex, to easy peasy things stuff. This can include sowing, tree planting, setting up new herb / vegetable zones, harvesting, bringing/making compost or fixing structures directly related to food production. We have plenty of tools, and can probably fetch some more if you feel that something important is missing. No specific knowledge prerequisites, but we will prefer responsible people who share our values. Let us know what you're good at, and we can discuss what could potentially be of interest and in alignment with
